It was necessary for tracing but as a traced model would have always taken the branch taken during tracing. In other words, it wouldn't have been possible to use the model with inputs of dimensions different to the example used during tracing and have an output with the right/expected dimension.
However, if we move this output shaping block in its own function, I am sure we could keep the old more readable logic and add the `torch.jit.scripting_if_tracing` decorator added to it. So the changes would be something like:

```python
